com.kontakt.sdk.ble.device

Interface IRegion

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Parcelable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Region

    public interface IRegion
extends Parcelable
    According to iOS naming convention Region is a geographical area defined by a circle of a specified radius around a known point on the Earth's surface. Being consistent with naming convention, the Region in Android SDK has theorethically the same meaning as the explanation given in Android SDK. Please note that our SDK contains also Venue which acts as Region with logic of kontakt.io included.
